doc.after: The three major languages spoken on Java are Javanese Sundanese and Madurese Other languages spoken include Betawi a Malay dialect local to the Jakarta region Osing Banyumasan and Tenggerese closely related to Javanese Baduy closely related to Sundanese Kangeanese closely related to Madurese and Balinese 36 The vast majority of the population also speaks Indonesian often as a second language
